ion of the atmospheric temperature profile\nand the calculation of the lifetime of the atmosphere. In the case of\nMASCARA-2b, residual features are observed in the H$\\beta$ and H$\\gamma$ lines,\nbut they are not statistically significant. More transit observations are\nneeded to confirm our findings in Na I and H$\\alpha$, and to build up enough\nS/N to explore the presence of H$\\beta$ and H$\\gamma$ planetary absorptions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 May 2018 15:23:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-12"}
